---
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";

import { type CollectionEntry, getCollection, render } from "astro:content";

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  const posts = await getCollection("clients");
  return posts.map((project) => ({
    params: { id: project.id },
    props: project,
  }));
}

const post = Astro.props;
// This gets the main content from the markdown file and 
// turns it into an Astro component: <Content />
const { Content } = await render(post);
---

<Layout title={post.data.title}>
  <nav>
    <div class="navR">
      <a class="navItm" href="/">Portfolio</a>
      <a class="navItm">Contact Me!</a>
    </div>
  </nav>
    <Container>
      <div class="contain">
        <h1>{post.data.title}</h1>
        <Content class="content" />
        <img src="/src/content/clients/awc/thumbnail.png" class="workImg"></img>

        <!-- example page content from AWC page -->
        <h2 class="subHead">Intramural Promotional Posters</h2>
        <p>Below here you can see some of the posters that I made for their intramural events advertising what is offered and giving instructions on how to sign up.</p>
        <div class="multiCol">
          <img src="/src/content/clients/awc/thumbnail.png" class="colImg"></img>
          <img src="/src/content/clients/awc/thumbnail.png" class="colImg"></img>
          <img src="/src/content/clients/awc/thumbnail.png" class="colImg"></img>
        </div>
        <h2 class="subHead">New Paltz Esports</h2>
        <p>Additionally through my Athletics internship I defined the design style for Esports at SUNY New Paltz. Below you can see the logo that I created to represent New Paltz Esports along with the same Athletics guidelines.</p>
        <img src="/src/content/clients/awc/thumbnail.png" class="workImg"></img>
        <p>Here you can see the posters and advertising materials I made for the Esports program through my time with the internship. I defined the design style for NP Esports to have the grainy background and sharp shapes to convey the same style of New Paltz but in a grittier, more competitive way.</p>
        <div class="multiCol">
          <img src="/src/content/clients/awc/thumbnail.png" class="colImg"></img>
          <img src="/src/content/clients/awc/thumbnail.png" class="colImg"></img>
          <img src="/src/content/clients/awc/thumbnail.png" class="colImg"></img>
        </div>
        <!-- ---------example end-------- -->

      </div>
    </Container>
  
</Layout>

<style>

  nav{
  position: sticky;
  top: -5px;
  paint-order: stroke fill;
  border-top: 5px solid yellow;
  border-bottom: 5px solid yellow;
  background-color: black;
  width: 100%;
  height: 8vh;
}

.navR{
  height: 100%;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-end;
  align-items: center;
  margin-right: 20px;
  gap: 20px;
}

.navItm{
  width: fit-content;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  flex-flow: row wrap;
  font-size: 30px;
  color: yellow;
  text-decoration: none;
}
.navItm:hover{ color: black; background-color: yellow;}

  .contain{
    padding: 30px;
  }

  .content{
    padding: 30px;
  }

  h1{
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    font-weight: 900;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 60px;
    margin-top: 60px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    text-decoration: underline;
    color: white;
  }

  .subHead{
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    margin: 20px;
    color: white;
    font-size: 36px;
    text-decoration: underline;
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  .workImg{
    max-width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    margin: 20px;
    border-bottom: 8px solid yellow;
    border-right: 5px solid yellow;
  }

  .colImg{
    max-width: 30%;
    height: auto;
    border-bottom: 5px solid yellow;
    border-right: 3px solid yellow;
  }

  p{
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .multiCol{
    display: flex;
    overflow: hidden;
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 30px;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }
</style>